premise_source_doc_sentence: Paternoster Row was a street in the City of London that is supposed to have received its name from the fact that , when the monks and clergy of St Paul 's Cathedral would go in procession chanting the great litany , they would recite the Lord 's Prayer  (  Pater Noster being its opening line in Latin  )  in the litany along this part of the route .
